sentence: Mars has four known co-orbital asteroids (5261 Eureka,, all at the Lagrangian point s), and Jupiter has many (an estimated one million greater than 1 km in diameter, the Jovian trojans); there are also other small co-orbital moons in the Saturnian system: Telesto and Calypso with Tethys, and Helene and Polydeuces with Dione.
